BSL is British Sign Language. It is used by the Deaf Community in the United Kingdom by England, Wales & Scottland.
However there was no law recognising BSL and there were many campaigns for it.
Rosie Cooper is a child of Deaf parents and is a member of Parliament in the House of Commons.
Rosie proposed a bill to recognise BSL in June 2021.
The bill was proposed in the House of Commons which is like India's Lok Sabha. The bill was then discussed by the members.
The BSL bill was then introduced by Christopher Holmes to the House of Lords which is like Rajya Sabha on March 2022.
In the House of Lords, at the 3rd reading of the bill on 27 April 2022 the bill was passed.
The BSL Bill has now become the BSL Act.
After years of campaigning people were very happy that BSL was finally recognised.
Generations of the Deaf community will leave hassle free because of this Act.

Malaria is a life-threatening disease
caused by parasites that are transmitted to people through the bites of infected female Anopheles mosquitoes.
It is preventable and curable.
Symptoms include fever, headaches and muscle pain, then cycles of chills and sweating.
The disease kills more than 4,00,000 people a year, mostly African children.
Malaria is a deadly disease.
Pharmaceutical company GSK had first made a vaccine against malaria in 1987.
The vaccine called RTS,S was proven effective six years ago.
In a pilot project in Ghana, Kenya and Malawi, two million doses of the vaccine were given to children.
This is because there are more than 100 types of malaria parasites.
